{
  "texts": [
    "Serrano et al. (2025) address this by introducing a causal transformer over discrete latent tokens, paired with an effective in-context pretraining strategy, allowing adaptation to new PDE regimes via in-context learning and probabilistic predictions.",
    "To evaluate the performance of ENMA, we generate several synthetic datasets based on diverse parametric PDEs in 1D and 2D.",
    "Each dataset consists of 12,000 trajectories for training.",
    "For evaluation, we generate two test sets: 1,200 trajectories for in-distribution (In-D) and 120 for out-ofdistribution (Out-D) evaluation.",
    "In the In-D case, test parameters γ differ from the training set but are sampled from the same distribution; in Out-D, they lie outside this range."
  ]
}